The paper deals with distributed algorithms for computing shortest paths on a network, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The bandwidth restriction on edges is a common constraint in network communication (cs.NI). The paper also presents approximation algorithms, which is a topic in approximation algorithms (cs.AL) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
